```
msteams://teams.microsoft.com/l/deeplink?path=/startPage&url=https://attacker.com/malicious
```

The `allowedHostNames` whitelist is **ECS-controlled** (remotely configurable), so it can be changed server-side to allow attacker domains without a Teams update.

